  <div class="page">
    <p>Problems</p>
    <p>Weak passwords are easy to crack</p>
    <p>Short, common, easy to guess (e.g., secret, susan123)</p>
    <p>Vulnerable to brute-force and dictionary attacks</p>
    <p>Users often choose weak passwords (easy to remember)</p>
    <p>Passwords are vulnerable to theft</p>
    <p>Phishing, key logging, shoulder surfing, etc.</p>
    <p>Even worse: more accounts, password sharing (6.5 over 25)</p>
